cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper deals with deep learning for object classification, specifically using convolutional models and attention mechanisms. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of exemplar-based cross-alignment, which involves learning a mechanism of alignment, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses open-set recognition, which could fall under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
